https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/4.3/registry/configuring_registry_storage/configuring-registry-storage-baremetal.html#configuring-registry-storage-baremetal

1.Created nfs storage class:
https://medium.com/faun/openshift-dynamic-nfs-persistent-volume-using-nfs-client-provisioner-fcbb8c9344e

oc adm policy add-cluster-role-to-user nfs-client-provisioner-runner system:serviceaccount:default:nfs-client-provisioner

3. Edit Storage class to reclaimPolicy: Retain

2. created a pvc with below content
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: image-registry-storage
  namespace: openshift-image-registry
spec:
  accessModes:
  - ReadWriteMany
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 200Gi
  storageClassName: managed-nfs-storage
  
3. oc edit configs.imageregistry.operator.openshift.io
Changed :
a) managementState: Removed -> managementState: Managed
b) storage:
         emptyDir: {}
   to
    storage:
         pvc:
           claim
           
4. oc get pods -n openshift-image-registry
You can verify the image-registry pod got created and claimed the pvc  image-registry-storage 


NFS Provisioner Setup:

https://github.com/ekambaraml/nfs-ocp43/blob/master/README.md


status:
  conditions:
  - lastTransitionTime: "2020-06-08T02:53:52Z"
    message: 'Unable to apply resources: unable to sync storage configuration: persistentvolumeclaims
      "image-registry-storage" not found'
